data.title: Dodge County, Georgia Population 2024
data.text:
Dodge County, Georgia 's estimated 2024 population is 19,679 with a growth rate of -0.49% in the past year according to the most recent United States census data. Dodge County, Georgia is the 96th largest county in Georgia. The 2010 population was 21,756 and has seen a growth of -9.55% since that time.

The highest rate of high school graduation is among native american people with a rate of 100% .

The highest rate of bachelors degrees is among white people with a rate of 20.12% .
